cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.DL, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with planar point location in a collection of disjoint regions, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus of the paper is on dynamic data structures that support local updates, which suggests that it could also be classified under data structures (cs.DS). The use of logarithmic time for queries and sub-logarithmic time for updates suggests that the paper could also be classified under algorithms and data structures (cs.DM) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper's focus on complexity analysis and pointer machines suggests that it could also be classified under computational complexity (cs.CC).
